3013 (((v_entry < 0.0f) || (v_exit > 0.0f)) ?
3014 // coasting
3015 (v_entry - v_exit) :
3016 // axis reversal
3017 std::max(-v_exit, v_entry));
3018
3019
3020 float axis_max_jerk = get_axis_max_jerk(static_cast<PrintEstimatedStatistics::ETimeMode>(i), static_cast<Axis>(a));
3021 if (jerk > axis_max_jerk) {
3022 v_factor *= axis_max_jerk / jerk;
3023 limited = true;
3024 }
3025 }
3026 }
3027
3028 if (limited)
3029 vmax_junction *= v_factor;
3030
3031 // Now the transition velocity is known, which maximizes the shared exit / entry velocity while
3032 // respecting the jerk factors, it may be possible, that applying separate safe exit / entry velocities will achieve faster prints.
3033 float vmax_junction_threshold = vmax_junction * 0.99f;
3034
3035 // Not coasting. The machine will stop and start the movements anyway, better to start the segment from start.
3036 if (prev.safe_feedrate > vmax_junction_threshold && curr.safe_feedrate > vmax_junction_threshold)
3037 vmax_junction = curr.safe_feedrate;
3038 }
3039
3040 float v_allowable = max_allowable_speed(-acceleration, curr.safe_feedrate, block.distance);
3041 block.feedrate_profile.entry = std::min(vmax_junction, v_allowable);
3042
3043 block.max_entry_speed = vmax_junction;
3044 block.flags.nominal_length = (block.feedrate_profile.cruise <= v_allowable);
3045 block.flags.recalculate = true;
3046 block.safe_feedrate = curr.safe_feedrate;
3047
3048 // calculates block trapezoid
3049 block.calculate_trapezoid();
3050
3051 // updates previous
3052 prev = curr;
3053
3054 blocks.push_back(block);
3055
3056 if (blocks.size() > TimeProcessor::Planner::refresh_threshold)
3057 machine.calculate_time(TimeProcessor::Planner::queue_size);
3058 }
3059
3060 if (m_seams_detector.is_active()) {
3061 // check for seam starting vertex
3062 if (type == EMoveType::Extrude && m_extrusion_role == erExternalPerimeter && !m_seams_detector.has_first_vertex()) {
3063 //BBS: m_result.moves.back().position has plate offset, must minus plate offset before calculate the real seam position
3064 const Vec3f real_first_pos = Vec3f(m_result.moves.back().position.x() - m_x_offset, m_result.moves.back().position.y() - m_y_offset, m_result.moves.back().position.z());
3065 m_seams_detector.set_first_vertex(real_first_pos - m_extruder_offsets[m_extruder_id]);
3066 }
3067 // check for seam ending vertex and store the resulting move
3068 else if ((type != EMoveType::Extrude || (m_extrusion_role != erExternalPerimeter && m_extrusion_role != erOverhangPerimeter)) && m_seams_detector.has_first_vertex()) {
3069 auto set_end_position = [this](const Vec3f& pos) {
3070 m_end_position[X] = pos.x(); m_end_position[Y] = pos.y(); m_end_position[Z] = pos.z();
3071 };
3072
3073 const Vec3f curr_pos(m_end_position[X], m_end_position[Y], m_end_position[Z]);
3074 //BBS: m_result.moves.back().position has plate offset, must minus plate offset before calculate the real seam position
3075 const Vec3f real_last_pos = Vec3f(m_result.moves.back().position.x() - m_x_offset, m_result.moves.back().position.y() - m_y_offset, m_result.moves.back().position.z());
3076 const Vec3f new_pos = real_last_pos - m_extruder_offsets[m_extruder_id];
3077 const std::optional<Vec3f> first_vertex = m_seams_detector.get_first_vertex();
3078 // the threshold value = 0.0625f == 0.25 * 0.25 is arbitrary, we may find some smarter condition later
3079
3080 if ((new_pos - *first_vertex).squaredNorm() < 0.0625f) {
3081 set_end_position(0.5f * (new_pos + *first_vertex));
3082 store_move_vertex(EMoveType::Seam);
3083 set_end_position(curr_pos);
3084 }
3085
3086 m_seams_detector.activate(false);
3087 }
3088 }
3089 else if (type == EMoveType::Extrude && m_extrusion_role == erExternalPerimeter) {
3090 m_seams_detector.activate(true);
3091 Vec3f plate_offset = {(float) m_x_offset, (float) m_y_offset, 0.0f};
3092 m_seams_detector.set_first_vertex(m_result.moves.back().position - m_extruder_offsets[m_extruder_id] - plate_offset);
3093 }
3094
3095 if (m_spiral_vase_active && !m_result.spiral_vase_layers.empty()) {
3096 if (m_result.spiral_vase_layers.back().first == FLT_MAX && delta_pos[Z] > 0.0)
3097 // replace layer height placeholder with correct value
3098 m_result.spiral_vase_layers.back().first = static_cast<float>(m_end_position[Z]);
3099 if (!m_result.moves.empty())
3100 m_result.spiral_vase_layers.back().second.second = m_result.moves.size() - 1;
3101 }
3102
3103 // store move
3104 store_move_vertex(type);
3105}
